Reasoning: The paper focuses on self-training, a semi-supervised technique commonly used in natural language processing tasks such as sentiment classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning algorithms and their performance, which suggests categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of corpora and similarity measures also suggests categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
